    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're programming a voice assistant that responds when someone says its wake word (like \"Hey, Assistant!\"). To simulate the assistant \"waking up\" multiple times day during the day, you'll write a function that prints the response and call it each time the assistant is triggered.\r\n\r\n1. Define a function called `wake_up_response()` that prints a message like:\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   🔊 I'm listening...\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. Call the function **three times** to represent the assistant activated three times in a day.\r\n\r\n3. Make sure the message appears exactly three times.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nFunctions let you program consistent behavior. If you ever want to update the message, you only need to do it in one place.\r\n\r\nUse the **UMPIRE** strategy to understand what the assistant should say, plan your message, test it, and explain your code.",
